document_title: Hypoglycemia: Causes, symptoms, complications and prevention
subsection_content: Hypoglycemia is a condition in which the amount of sugar (glucose) in the blood falls below 70 mg/dL. The body's normal blood sugar level before eating ranges from 90 - 130 mg/dL, between meals 70 mg/dL to 100 mg/dL, and 1-2 hours after eating must be below 180 mg/dL. (first)

ha duong huyet.json. What is hypoglycemia?
Hypoglycemia is a condition in which the amount of sugar (glucose) in the blood falls below 70 mg/dL. The body's normal blood sugar level before eating ranges from 90 - 130 mg/dL, between meals 70 mg/dL to 100 mg/dL, and 1-2 hours after eating must be below 180 mg/dL. (first)
